      "role": "user",
      "content": "that middle ground sounds good in theory but it's hard to see how it works in real life. like, if the school says they HAVE to teach it for safety or inclusivity reasons, then the parents are basically just being told they don't have a say anymore. do you think the school's position is more 'correct' because they're looking out for all the kids in the building, or is the parent's right to decide for their own kid more important? it feels like one side has to be wrong for the other to be right.",
