      "content": "This is a classic conflict between individual rights and collective responsibility, and it is inherently difficult to resolve with a single \"correct\" answer. School administrations prioritize creating an environment where all children feel safe and respected, which is a duty of the institution. Conversely, parents assert their fundamental right to guide their children's values and worldview. In practice, the tension arises because both perspectives claim moral high ground, making compromise incredibly challenging.",
